HEADWORD: Inpatient
<hw>In"pa`tient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A patient who
receives lodging and food, as well as treatment, in a hospital or an
infirmary; -- distinguished from <contr>outpatient</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

